page.title: 19WILDLIFE IN THE WOODLANDS
page.content: In the woodland the worst enemies to the trees are{rabbits}because they eat the baby trees.The foresters {trap } rabbits or {shoot}them to keep the population down. Another pest is the{red deer}because it rubs its velvet off and in doing that it damages the bark and inside of the trees.The hunters only kill 4 or 5 {deer}a year out of a herd of about 50. There are also a few{roe deer}. The{woodpecker}does good to the trees because it eats the beetles inside the trees.{Grey squirrels} live in the trees.Their nests are called { {dreys}.They eat the cones and the tops of trees. There are also {badgers}in the woods which make large holes in the ground called {setts}.Sometimes there are rare birds like the{hobby}.
